<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="412" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="27.[813,1455,1123,1174]" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">
COLLECTOR/S. — Charles-Alexandre Lesueur, 
<emphasis box="[1258,1316,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">contra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Girard" firstAuthor="Girard" page="114" pageId="27" pageNumber="412" refId="ref36703" refString="GIRARD M. 1856. - F. Peron, naturaliste, voyageur aux Terres Australes; sa vie, appreciation de ses travaux, analyse raisonnee de ses recherches sur les animaux vertebres et invertebres d'apres ses collections depos e es au Museum d'Histoire naturelle. J. - B. Bailliere, Paris. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 46101762" type="url" year="1856">Girard (1856: 114)</bibRefCitation>
who mentioned Péron as its collector.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[811,1456,1198,1434]" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">
COLLECTION LOCALITY. — Near Port Jackson (Sydney), 
<collectingRegion country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[882,968,1224,1248]" name="Australia" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Girard" box="[983,1161,1224,1248]" firstAuthor="Girard" page="114" pageId="27" pageNumber="412" refId="ref36703" refString="GIRARD M. 1856. - F. Peron, naturaliste, voyageur aux Terres Australes; sa vie, appreciation de ses travaux, analyse raisonnee de ses recherches sur les animaux vertebres et invertebres d'apres ses collections depos e es au Museum d'Histoire naturelle. J. - B. Bailliere, Paris. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 46101762" type="url" year="1856">Girard 1856: 114</bibRefCitation>
). One animal was taken alive back to 
<collectingCountry box="[887,951,1251,1274]" name="France" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">France</collectingCountry>
on board 
<emphasis box="[1045,1168,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">Le Géographe</emphasis>
under the name of “Kanguroo géant” (É. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire 1804c: 172). 
<bibRefCitation author="Girard" box="[1268,1455,1277,1301]" firstAuthor="Girard" page="114" pageId="27" pageNumber="412" refId="ref36703" refString="GIRARD M. 1856. - F. Peron, naturaliste, voyageur aux Terres Australes; sa vie, appreciation de ses travaux, analyse raisonnee de ses recherches sur les animaux vertebres et invertebres d'apres ses collections depos e es au Museum d'Histoire naturelle. J. - B. Bailliere, Paris. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 46101762" type="url" year="1856">Girard (1856: 114)</bibRefCitation>
reported that Péron brought back a living individual that perished on arrival and was dissected by G. Cuvier. According to a letter from Baudin, during the second break in Timor, there they had ten giant kangaroos alive on 
<emphasis box="[998,1123,1383,1407]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">Le Géographe</emphasis>
but only one was left upon arrival in 
<collectingCountry box="[839,904,1410,1433]" name="France" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Girard" box="[918,1093,1409,1434]" firstAuthor="Girard" page="114" pageId="27" pageNumber="412" refId="ref36703" refString="GIRARD M. 1856. - F. Peron, naturaliste, voyageur aux Terres Australes; sa vie, appreciation de ses travaux, analyse raisonnee de ses recherches sur les animaux vertebres et invertebres d'apres ses collections depos e es au Museum d'Histoire naturelle. J. - B. Bailliere, Paris. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 46101762" type="url" year="1856">Girard 1856: 114</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[813,1452,1457,1482]" box="[813,1452,1457,1482]" pageId="27" pageNumber="412">
COLLECTION DATE. — Between 
<date box="[1128,1448,1457,1481]" pageId="27" pageNumber="412" value="1802-06-20" valueMax="1802-11-18" valueMin="1802-06-20">20 June and 18 November 1802</date>
.
</paragraph>
